.TH "ib_umem_get" 9 "ib_umem_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_umem_get \- Pin and DMA map userspace memory.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ib_umem *" ib_umem_get
.BI "(struct ib_device *device "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "int access "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
IB device to connect UMEM
.IP "addr" 12
userspace virtual address to start at
.IP "size" 12
length of region to pin
.IP "access" 12
IB_ACCESS_xxx flags for memory being pinned
